Description: Tilt-controlled harmonium instrument for the Linux terminal
 realharmonium turns your laptop into a virtual harmonium.
 .
 Tilt your laptop screen forward and back to pump the bellows —
 just like a real harmonium — while playing notes on the keyboard.
 .
 Features:
  - 4-layer reed synthesis (sawtooth + detuned overtones) via numpy + pygame
  - Linux IIO accelerometer integration for true tilt detection
  - Full-terminal curses interface with animated bellows meter
  - Sa drone mode (continuous C + G bass drone)
  - Zero dependencies beyond numpy and pygame
